  "prompt": "What are determinant of demand and supply?",
  "response": "Determinants of Demand and Supply are factors that can cause shifts in the demand or supply curves, affecting the equilibrium price and quantity of a good or service. Here's a detailed breakdown:\n\nDeterminants of Demand:\n1. Income\n- Affects purchasing power\n- Normal goods: increases in income lead to higher demand\n- Inferior goods: increases in income lead to lower demand\n\n2. Prices of Related Goods\n- Substitutes: price increase leads to higher demand for alternatives\n- Complements: price increase leads to lower demand for related goods\n\n3. Consumer Preferences\n- Tastes and trends\n- Cultural factors\n- Advertising\n\n4. Population\n- Number of potential consumers\n- Demographic changes\n\n5. Expectations\n- Future price expectations\n- Economic outlook\n\nDeterminants of Supply:\n1. Production Costs\n- Raw material prices\n- Labor costs\n- Technology\n- Energy expenses\n\n2. Technology\n- Improved production methods\n- Innovation\n- Efficiency gains\n\n3. Number of Sellers\n- Market entry or exit\n- Competitive landscape\n\n4. Government Policies\n- Taxes\n- Subsidies\n- Regulations\n\n5. Expected Future Prices\n- Potential profit opportunities\n- Market predictions\n\nUnderstanding these determinants helps analyze market dynamics and predict potential shifts in demand and supply curves.",
